cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper addresses the problem of personalizing query completion in a digital commerce setting, which is a core problem in information retrieval. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes to improve the standard noisy channel model by injecting dense vectors computed from product images at query time, which involves computer vision techniques. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a personalized type-ahead system, which involves machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed methods and provides qualitative support, which involves natural language processing techniques. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper proposes to use product images to improve the personalized type-ahead system, which involves multimedia techniques.
